(coherent/charged-bath variant: dm2_amb = C_coh*e^2 = -0.01275 at e=0.8, K^-component only)

=== (6) effective metric / photon-speed corrections at e_bath=0.8 ===
photon: v^2 = 0.888889 -> 0.888609; d(v^2) = -2.80e-04
  (eta^2*dm2/m2^2 = -2.79e-04, F9 agrees)
matter g^ij_perp = (1+eta^2/(m2+dm2)) = 1.111391 (vac 1.111111)
coherent-bath birefringence (k perp K^): Delta(m_eff^2) between polarizations = |C_coh| e^2 = 0.01275 at e=0.8

=== (7) motion through bath: relative-mass anisotropy [estimate] ===
isotropic on-shell bath, ball velocity v: e_bath -> gamma^2(1+v^2/3) e
dm2(v) = dm2(0) * gamma^4 (1+v^2/3)^2  ~  dm2(0) * (1 + 8 v^2/3)  (O(v^2))
  v=0.1: dm2(v)/dm2(0) = 1.0271  (O(v^2) approx 1.0267)
  v=0.3: dm2(v)/dm2(0) = 1.2811  (O(v^2) approx 1.2400)
  v=0.5: dm2(v)/dm2(0) = 2.0864  (O(v^2) approx 1.6667)

=== consistency cross-checks ===
2x2 eigencheck at K=1.4: photon W^2=1.760000, matter 4.410000 : PASS
F8c on-shell closed form: dm2 = mu eta^4 e^2/(4 m2^4) = -0.02521 e^2 : PASS
